oted to a description of ‘the system’ using phase diagrams. The second explores the properties and uses of some of the minerals that are in widespread industrial and commercial use. Much of the work presented in this book is fully original and corresponds to the research undertaken by François Sorrentino from his time at the chemistry department of the University of Aberdeen during the early 1970’s, to recent years when he has resumed his interest in mineral research, particularly related to the synthesis of calcium silicates and calcium aluminates, and their industrial manufacture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aOxides. 4amaterial sciences. 7aSCIENCE / Chemistry / General.2bisacsh1 aDamidot, Denis, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFentiman, Charles, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021 Englishz978311075416208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021z9783110753936oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Frontlist eBook Package 2021z97831107566540 cprintz978275982480940uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-2536-340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759825363423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782759825363/original  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075416-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075665-4  ED